gime as well as a survey-based study of nationalism in public opinion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNationalismzFormer Soviet republics. 0aNationalismzRussia (Federation) 0aNationalismzRussia (Federation). 0aRussiansxEthnic identity. 4aPolitics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism & Patriotism.2bisacsh1 aAlexseev, Mikhail A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlakkisrud, Helge, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBlakkisrud, Helge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHale, Henry E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutchings, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolstø, Pål, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKosmarskaya, Natalya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaruelle, Marlene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitrofanova, Anastasia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPain, Emil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRutland, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSavin, Igor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTolz, Vera, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVerkhovsky, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311078044440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474410434?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474410434423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474410434/original  